cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.IT 

This paper deals with the problem of overload control in SIP networks, which is related to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The proposed Load-Balanced Call Admission Controller (LB-CAC) is based on a mathematical model, which involves optimization techniques (cs.SY) and heuristic approaches (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the acquisition of critical information from SIP servers, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
